    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-04-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-04-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="551"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d551">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Lane</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-04-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 11, 1899</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I append hereto copy of your telegram<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d551fn1">Printed ante.</note> of the 5th instant, and of this
                    Department’s reply of the 6th, as well as copies of telegrams to Mr. Merry, all
                    relating to affairs at Bluefields.</p>
                <p>Referring to the statement in your telegram, that you are unable to communicate
                    with the minister, you are instructed to ask, should your telegrams be
                    interfered with, instant permission to send and receive official telegrams.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
